<div id="autonomous-endpoint-management" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">
      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="page-hero-content">
          <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
            <h4>Autonomous endpoint management</h4>
            <h1>Patch faster than threats can spread</h1>
          </div>
          <div purpose="page-hero-text">
            <p>Vulnerabilities are now exploited 100x faster than three years ago. Fleet's autonomous endpoint management cuts patch cycles from 55 to 94 days down to under two weeks, with humans still in the loop.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="button-row" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <a purpose="cta-button" href="/contact?sendMessage" no-underline>Talk to us</a>
            <a purpose="video-button"  @click="clickOpenVideoModal('fleet-in-three-minutes')"><img alt="Play" class="d-inline" src="/images/icon-play-video-32x32@2x.png">See Fleet in action <span>3 mins</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div><%/* landing-page-hero */%>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>The patch cycle is broken</h3>
          <p>IT teams are stuck between accelerating threats and manual patching processes that haven't kept up. The gap creates risk no team can close by hiring more humans.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="four-column-feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Velocity vs. disruption</h5>
            <p>Faster updates protect the org but break workflows. Slower updates protect users but expose the business.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>"No news" isn't good news</h5>
            <p>Less than 50% of employees report issues to the help desk. Silence isn't proof a patch worked.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Manual everything</h5>
            <p>Identifying, testing, ringing, and promoting patches still relies on intuition and tickets.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>AI-accelerated threats</h5>
            <p>A vulnerability disclosed Friday can be weaponized by Monday. Tools built for monthly cycles can't keep up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="stat-callout">
          <div purpose="stat-block">
            <p purpose="stat-number">87%</p>
            <p purpose="stat-label">Reduction in patch cycle time with autonomous endpoint management.<sup>1</sup></p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="stat-block">
            <p purpose="stat-number">6 to 13</p>
            <p purpose="stat-label">Days to remediate with AEM, down from 55 to 94 days without it.<sup>1</sup></p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="stat-block">
            <p purpose="stat-number">50%+</p>
            <p purpose="stat-label">Of organizations will adopt AEM by 2029, up from nearly zero in 2024.<sup>1</sup></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p purpose="stat-source"><sup>1</sup> Gartner, Innovation Insight: Autonomous Endpoint Management, January 2025 (G00804840).</p>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet automatically patching software based on policy" src="/images/feature-image-automate-patch-management-1056x754@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>What Fleet does</h3>
            <p>Fleet monitors when new software updates become available and when new vulnerabilities are disclosed. When a device falls out of compliance, Fleet automatically updates the software or applies a more advanced mitigation, like uninstalling the old version. No ticket, no manual intervention.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Hourly policy evaluation across installed software, configuration state, and system metrics, on every OS</p>
              <p>Automatic software updates and advanced mitigations when devices fall out of compliance</p>
              <p>Customizable auto-patch policies with ring deployments, scoping, exclusions, and variations by role, subsidiary, or geography</p>
              <p>Out-of-the-box reporting on Mean Time to Patch (MTTP) and exposure windows for critical vulnerabilities</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <p purpose="quote-text">&ldquo;Adopting Fleet has fundamentally shifted how we manage devices. We've unlocked total, unified visibility across thousands of employee devices, and we get real-time confidence in the health and compliance of our global infrastructure every single day.&rdquo;</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <div purpose="quote-author-image">
              <img alt="Dan Jackson" src="/images/testimonial-author-dan-jackson-48x48@2x.png">
            </div>
            <p purpose="author-name">Dan Jackson</p>
            <p purpose="author-title">Senior Manager, Systems Engineering at Fastly</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>How Fleet's autonomous patching works</h3>
          <p>Fleet's policy engine replaces manual, ticket-driven patching with hourly automation that you fully customize.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="aem-flow">
          <div purpose="flow-step">
            <div purpose="step-number">1</div>
            <p purpose="step-title">Detect</p>
            <p>Fleet's policy engine compares installed software, configuration state, and system metrics with known vulnerability databases and the latest available software releases. Policies run hourly, on every OS, or at any custom interval you define.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="flow-step">
            <div purpose="step-number">2</div>
            <p purpose="step-title">Remediate</p>
            <p>When a device falls out of compliance, Fleet automatically installs the correct software version, or applies a more advanced mitigation such as uninstalling the old version. No ticket required.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="flow-step">
            <div purpose="step-number">3</div>
            <p purpose="step-title">Roll out in rings</p>
            <p>Stage updates across deployment rings with complex scoping, exclusions, and variations for particular roles, subsidiaries, or global geographies. Roll out fast where you need to, carefully where you must.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="flow-step">
            <div purpose="step-number">4</div>
            <p purpose="step-title">Report</p>
            <p>Out-of-the-box dashboards show which devices are currently out of date and how long they were exposed to critical vulnerabilities over the last 30 days. Pipe data to your data lake for deeper historical analysis.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Built for modern endpoint teams</h2>
          <p>Fleet's autonomous capabilities ship in every license. Not as a separate product, not as an upsell.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Out-of-the-box exposure reporting</h5>
            <p>See which devices have been out of date and how long they were exposed to critical CVEs over the last 30 days. Calculate MTTP without building it yourself.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Upgraded policy engine</h5>
            <p>Policies run hourly (or at any interval you choose) and automatically install updates or apply mitigations when devices fall out of compliance.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Customizable auto-patch policies</h5>
            <p>Configure ring deployments, exclusions, scoping, and variations by role, subsidiary, or geography. Roll out fast where you need to, carefully where you must.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Advanced mitigations</h5>
            <p>When a simple update isn't enough, Fleet can perform more advanced mitigations, such as uninstalling the old version of an affected app.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Data lake integrations</h5>
            <p>Send Fleet's data to your existing data lake for infinite, more in-depth historical analysis of exposure and patch activity.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Every major OS</h5>
            <p>One platform, one policy engine, one inventory across macOS, Windows, Linux, iOS, iPadOS, Android, ChromeOS, and cloud infrastructure.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image" class="reverse">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet's GitOps workflow showing a pull request reviewing a configuration change" src="/images/fleet-gitops-workflow-471x337@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>Autonomous, with humans still in charge</h3>
            <p>Fleet has prioritized change control and GitOps-mode from the very beginning. As auto-patching becomes inevitable, auditability, undo-ability, and special exceptions matter even more, especially at tens of thousands of devices.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Manage profiles, policies, and software in version-controlled YAML</p>
              <p>Review every change in a pull request before it ships</p>
              <p>Roll back any configuration change with a single git revert</p>
              <p>Open codebase your security team can audit and your engineers can extend</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <p purpose="quote-text">&ldquo;Now that auto-patching is becoming inevitable for every organization, auditability, undo-ability, and special exceptions are even more important, especially for large enterprises where you're managing tens of thousands of devices. You need humans in the loop to prevent costly mistakes and outages, and Fleet's implementation of autonomous endpoint management provides that middle ground.&rdquo;</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <p purpose="author-name">Mike McNeil</p>
            <p purpose="author-title">Cofounder and CEO, Fleet</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <p purpose="quote-text">&ldquo;Patch policies are already transforming how we operate. Apps we'd skip patching due to maintenance overhead are now straightforward to configure, typically taking just five minutes. The ongoing maintenance burden is minimal, and I can set it up to update software automatically while still customizing every aspect of the end user experience.&rdquo;</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <p purpose="author-name">Principal endpoint engineer</p>
            <p purpose="author-title">Leading consumer electronics company</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What people are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>
  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">
    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Autonomous endpoint management</h4>
        <h1>Stay ahead of threats. Without losing sleep.</h1>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="mr-0" href="/contact" no-underline>Get a demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
